FBIS4-62393 "drsov094_b_94030" FBIS-SOV-94-094 Daily Report 13 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Missile, Artillery Academy Presidium Holds First Session Missile, Artillery Academy Presidium Holds First Session PM1305131594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 13 May 94 First Edition p 1 PM1305131594 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [Report by Nikolai Burbyga: "Development of `Intellectual' Weapons One of the Main Military-Technical Priorities"] [Text] The first session of the presidium of the Russian Academy of Missile and Artillery Science, recently resurrected by an edict of the Russian president, has been held in Moscow. First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey Kokoshin stressed that this academy is designed to be an important organ uniting leading scientists of various specialities engaged in developing promising technologies for arms systems using artillery and missile weapons. Among the military-technical projects which are being implemented first place goes to the creation of "intellectual" weapons systems capable of striking primarily the "nerve centers" of the other side's armed forces and taking out the enemy's complex equipment.
